08/04/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro will be host the Southeast European Co-operation Process (SEECP) summit on Wednesday (9 April). The presidents of Macedonia, Bulgaria, Albania, Romania, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro and the prime ministers of Greece and Turkey will meet in Belgrade to discuss measures to fight organised crime, as well as free trade, energy, traffic and telecommunications issues. A meeting of the foreign ministers will take place on Tuesday. The EU, the OSCE, the UN and the Council of Europe are expected to send representatives. (AP, AFP - 07/04/03)
